That said, unlike Francis, I learned early on to enter words that I know aren't the answer to rule out letters when there are too many choices left. Otherwise, it becomes simply a game of luck, and I hate losing a streak just because I had _ATCH and guessed B, C, and L when the answer was P.  PLUMB is a good one in this case.

