@B

Right. In any of those cases I would probably just say open/unlocked/ajar. Unshut just sounds wrong.

Polish syntax works slightly differently than English. In Polish, "You left the door/fridge/whatever [unshut]" would usually be styled as "Nie zamknąłeś/zamknęłaś drzwi/lodówki/czegokolwiek" - literally, "You did not lock/shut the door/fridge/whatever". Zamknąłeś is the masculine, and zamknęłaś the feminine version. "Zostawiłeś drzwi otwarte", you left the door unlocked, would be understood just fine, too, but it sounds slightly awkward.

